Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Pour enough @olive oil{} into a deep #baking tray{} to cover the bottom and pop into the oven.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} on high heat with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Peel and chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 3cm chunks.

Add the potatoes to the boiling water and boil for ~{5-6%minutes} or until the edges are soft.

Meanwhile, pick the @tarragon{1/2%bunch} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Halve the @mangetout{150%g} widthways.

Once the potatoes are ready, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan.

Sprinkle on the @plain flour{1%tbsp} and @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Shake to fluff up the potatoes, then carefully add them to the hot baking tray, turning in the oil.

Season with @salt{}, then roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Season the @British chicken breasts{2} with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Once hot, lay the chicken into the pan and cook until browned, ~{3-5%minutes} each side.

Once browned, transfer to a #baking tray{} and roast on the top shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When cooked, remove the chicken from your oven, cover with #foil{} and allow to rest for a couple of ~{minutes}.

Pop the (now empty) frying pan on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{} if needed.

Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g}. Stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{75%g}, tarragon, @chicken stock paste{5%g}, @water for the sauce{100%ml} and half the @wholegrain mustard{17%g}.

Simmer until the sauce has thickened slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

While the sauce simmers, in a large #bowl{}, combine the @red wine vinegar{12%ml}, remaining mustard, @sugar for the dressing{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil for the dressing{1%tbsp}.

Add the mangetout, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then mix together.

When everything's nearly ready, add the @pea shoots{40%g} to the bowl of dressing and toss to coat.

Once the chicken has rested, cut widthways into 2cm slices and transfer to your plates.

Taste the creamy sauce and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed, adding a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Serve the chicken with the roast potatoes and salad alongside. Spoon the sauce over the chicken to finish.

Enjoy!